``` CodeBlock_CodeBlockPre__E56UT
import * as React from "react";
import { Dialog } from "radix-ui";
import { Cross2Icon } from "@radix-ui/react-icons";
import "./styles.css";

const DialogDemo = () => (
   <Dialog.Root>
        <Dialog.Trigger asChild>
            <button className="Button violet">Edit profile</button>
       </Dialog.Trigger>
       <Dialog.Portal>
           <Dialog.Overlay className="DialogOverlay" />
           <Dialog.Content className="DialogContent">
               <Dialog.Title className="DialogTitle">Edit profile</Dialog.Title>
               <Dialog.Description className="DialogDescription">
                   Make changes to your profile here. Click save when you're done.
               </Dialog.Description>
               <fieldset className="Fieldset">
                   <label className="Label" htmlFor="name">
                       Name
                   </label>
                   <input className="Input" id="name" defaultValue="Pedro Duarte" />
               </fieldset>
               <fieldset className="Fieldset">
                   <label className="Label" htmlFor="username">
                       Username
                   </label>
                   <input className="Input" id="username" defaultValue="@peduarte" />
               </fieldset>
               <div
                    style={{ display: "flex", marginTop: 25, justifyContent: "flex-end" }}
                >
                   <Dialog.Close asChild>
                       <button className="Button green">Save changes</button>
                   </Dialog.Close>
               </div>
               <Dialog.Close asChild>
                   <button className="IconButton" aria-label="Close">
                       <Cross2Icon />
                   </button>
               </Dialog.Close>
           </Dialog.Content>
       </Dialog.Portal>
   </Dialog.Root>
);

export default DialogDemo;
```

``` CodeBlock_CodeBlockPre__E56UT
import { Dialog } from "radix-ui";

export default () => (
   <Dialog.Root>
        <Dialog.Trigger />
        <Dialog.Portal>
            <Dialog.Overlay />
            <Dialog.Content>
                <Dialog.Title />
               <Dialog.Description />
               <Dialog.Close />
           </Dialog.Content>
       </Dialog.Portal>
   </Dialog.Root>
);
```

### <a href="#close-after-asynchronous-form-submission" id="close-after-asynchronous-form-submission" class="rt-Text rt-reset rt-Link rt-r-weight-bold rt-underline-hover rt-high-contrast MDXComponents_LinkHeading__rCgOs" data-accent-color="gray">Close after asynchronous form submission<img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," /></a>

Use the controlled props to programmatically close the Dialog after an async operation has completed.

<div class="rt-Box rt-r-my-5 CodeBlock_CodeBlockRoot__kZw8W">

<div class="rt-Box CodeBlock_CodeBlockContent__tJMP_" code-block-content="true">

<div class="rt-ScrollAreaRoot" dir="ltr" style="position:relative;--radix-scroll-area-corner-width:0px;--radix-scroll-area-corner-height:0px">

<div class="rt-ScrollAreaViewport" radix-scroll-area-viewport="" style="overflow-x:hidden;overflow-y:hidden">

<div style="min-width:100%;display:table">

``` CodeBlock_CodeBlockPre__E56UT
import * as React from "react";
import { Dialog } from "radix-ui";

const wait = () => new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, 1000));

export default () => {
    const [open, setOpen] = React.useState(false);

   return (
       <Dialog.Root open={open} onOpenChange={setOpen}>
           <Dialog.Trigger>Open</Dialog.Trigger>
           <Dialog.Portal>
               <Dialog.Overlay />
               <Dialog.Content>
                    <form
                        onSubmit={(event) => {
                            wait().then(() => setOpen(false));
                            event.preventDefault();
                        }}
                    >
                       {/** some inputs */}
                        <button type="submit">Submit</button>
                   </form>
               </Dialog.Content>
           </Dialog.Portal>
       </Dialog.Root>
  );
};
```

</div>

### <a href="#custom-portal-container" id="custom-portal-container" class="rt-Text rt-reset rt-Link rt-r-weight-bold rt-underline-hover rt-high-contrast MDXComponents_LinkHeading__rCgOs" data-accent-color="gray">Custom portal container<img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," /></a>

``` CodeBlock_CodeBlockPre__E56UT
import * as React from "react";
import { Dialog } from "radix-ui";

export default () => {
    const [container, setContainer] = React.useState(null);
   return (
       <div>
            <Dialog.Root>
                <Dialog.Trigger />
                <Dialog.Portal container={container}>
                   <Dialog.Overlay />
                   <Dialog.Content>...</Dialog.Content>
               </Dialog.Portal>
           </Dialog.Root>

            <div ref={setContainer} />
       </div>
  );
};
```

## <a href="#custom-apis" id="custom-apis" class="rt-Text rt-reset rt-Link rt-r-weight-bold rt-underline-hover rt-high-contrast MDXComponents_LinkHeading__rCgOs" data-accent-color="gray">Custom APIs<img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," /></a>

Create your own API by abstracting the primitive parts into your own component.

### <a href="#abstract-the-overlay-and-the-close-button" id="abstract-the-overlay-and-the-close-button" class="rt-Text rt-reset rt-Link rt-r-weight-bold rt-underline-hover rt-high-contrast MDXComponents_LinkHeading__rCgOs" data-accent-color="gray">Abstract the overlay and the close button<img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," /></a>

This example abstracts the `Dialog.Overlay` and `Dialog.Close` parts.

#### Usage

<div class="rt-Box rt-r-my-5 CodeBlock_CodeBlockRoot__kZw8W">

<div class="rt-Box CodeBlock_CodeBlockContent__tJMP_" code-block-content="true">

<div class="rt-ScrollAreaRoot" dir="ltr" style="position:relative;--radix-scroll-area-corner-width:0px;--radix-scroll-area-corner-height:0px">

``` CodeBlock_CodeBlockPre__E56UT
import { Dialog, DialogTrigger, DialogContent } from "./your-dialog";

export default () => (
   <Dialog>
        <DialogTrigger>Dialog trigger</DialogTrigger>
        <DialogContent>Dialog Content</DialogContent>
    </Dialog>
);
```

#### Implementation

<div class="rt-Box rt-r-my-5 CodeBlock_CodeBlockRoot__kZw8W">

<div class="rt-Box CodeBlock_CodeBlockContent__tJMP_" code-block-content="true">

<div class="rt-ScrollAreaRoot" dir="ltr" style="position:relative;--radix-scroll-area-corner-width:0px;--radix-scroll-area-corner-height:0px">

<div class="rt-ScrollAreaViewport" radix-scroll-area-viewport="" style="overflow-x:hidden;overflow-y:hidden">

``` CodeBlock_CodeBlockPre__E56UT
// your-dialog.jsx
import * as React from "react";
import { Dialog as DialogPrimitive } from "radix-ui";
import { Cross1Icon } from "@radix-ui/react-icons";

export const DialogContent = React.forwardRef(
   ({ children, ...props }, forwardedRef) => (
       <DialogPrimitive.Portal>
            <DialogPrimitive.Overlay />
           <DialogPrimitive.Content {...props} ref={forwardedRef}>
               {children}
               <DialogPrimitive.Close aria-label="Close">
                   <Cross1Icon />
               </DialogPrimitive.Close>
           </DialogPrimitive.Content>
       </DialogPrimitive.Portal>
  ),
);

export const Dialog = DialogPrimitive.Root;
export const DialogTrigger = DialogPrimitive.Trigger;
```
